{
  "_readme": [
    "ModHarbor catalog — how to add a real mod:",
    "Copy a slot below, fill in the fields, and set 'status' to 'available' (or delete the status line).",
    "The app ignores this _readme block; only the 'mods' array is read.",
    "",
    "minimum_version — optional. Installed app versions below this value are forced to update",
    "before using ModHarbor (set when you ship breaking changes). Example: \"1.0.14\".",
    "",
    "Field reference:",
    "  id             — unique string, lowercase-with-dashes (e.g. 'realistic-handling-v2'). Never reuse an id.",
    "  game_id        — 'gta5' (only supported game right now).",
    "  name           — display name shown on the mod card.",
    "  author         — creator name shown as 'by <author>'.",
    "  description    — 1-2 sentence summary shown on the card.",
    "  thumbnail_url  — https URL to a 640x360 image. Leave '' to show a gray placeholder.",
    "  download_url   — direct https link to the mod .zip (source 'hosted'), or the mod's webpage (source 'external_link').",
    "  category       — one of: 'vehicles', 'weapons', 'characters', 'maps', 'scripts_trainers', 'visual_graphics'.",
    "  source         — 'hosted' = one-click install from download_url. 'external_link' = opens download_url in the browser.",
    "  download_count — number shown on the card (0 is fine for new mods).",
    "  version        — display version string (e.g. '1.2.0').",
    "  status         — 'coming_soon' renders a skeleton placeholder slot. 'available' (or omitted) makes it installable."
  ],
